{"document_name": "MSA-Helios-Cloud.docx", "edits": [{"new_text": "Helios shall have no right to use the Customer Data other than as necessary to provide and support the Services, and shall not sell or disclose Customer Data except as required by law.

7.4 INDEMNIFICATION
Each party (the "Indemnifying Party") shall indemnify, defend and hold harmless the other party and its affiliates against any and all third-party claims, losses, damages, liabilities and expenses (including reasonable legal fees) arising from a claim that the Indemnifying Party's materials (the Platform and Services in the case of Helios; the Customer Data and Customer's other materials in the case of the Customer) infringe a third party's intellectual property rights. In addition, the Customer shall indemnify, defend and hold harmless Helios and its affiliates against any and all third-party claims, losses, damages, liabilities and expenses (including reasonable legal fees) arising from or in connection with the Customer Data or the Customer's use of the Services in breach of this Agreement.", "rationale": "The MSA currently has no indemnification clause — a material gap. A mutual IP indemnity protects both sides against third-party infringement claims; the Customer Data indemnity protects Helios against claims from Customer's data or misuse. This is standard enterprise SaaS scope.", "target_text": "Helios shall have no right to use the Customer Data other than as necessary to provide and support the Services, and shall not sell or disclose Customer Data except as required by law."}]}
